title: For Sale:  Colt M1911 - WW1 Reproduction - Charcoal Blue Finish - New
postcontent:
Hi, 

Listed here is Colt M1911 reproduction, the World War I model. It's in beautiful carbonia / charcoal blue finish. 

This is essentially a Colt made, limited production 1911 pistol, meant to reproduce the original mil spec Colt 1911 of the early 20th century teens. It is chambered in .45 ACP, and bears all the build quality and aesthetic perfection one would expect from Colt. Only around 4,000 were made of this gun, and then another 4,000 of the 1918 version, which is finished in Black Oxide per the specs for wartime production of the pistol, before parkerized guns were adopted. 

This gun is in new condition, and is unfired. Never has been loaded either. Cosmetically and functionally, it is in perfect condition. There is very slight wear on the barrel lugs, and near the muzzle end of the barrel, but finish wear is to be expected in these areas, and is the result of a few dozen safety checks over time. I have seen other new examples of this same gun, but with more wear in those same areas. 

The charcoal finished version of this gun is generally a little more sought after than the black oxide version of the M1911, as the carbonia / charcoal is a more choice process, offering a look that compliments the 1911 like no other. Furthermore, the WW1 reproductions have met with a very large amount critical and popular acclaim during the past few years. They rate high as accurate reproductions of the original pistol, and as VERY shootable, and an incredibly well made GI 1911 configuration 1911 from Colt. If you know Colts and like 1911s, you are probably enlightened as to how wonderful these pieces are. If you are new to these, please look them up and prepare to be intrigued. 

The trigger on this gun is incredible. I previously owned a 1918 version of this same gun, and it shot incredibly well, with no jams, or failures. But the trigger is what's best, as it's less than 4 pounds, and really touches off at that perfect moment, basically helping the shooter in chewing a two inch wide hole through through the target. If you can shoot, then this gun won't hold you back in performance. There are other mil spec Colt that are really heavy in comparison. This one is not. It's on par with most custom-grade 1911s, and should prove to be a great shooter. 

The sale includes the gun, two unstamped repro - style Colt mags (standard blued, single tone), the military style issue box (see pics), and a reprint of the original Colt 1911 manual. There are a few extras that originally came with the gun that are not included: These 1911s were produced via Colt's custom shop, and came inside the Colt CS blue box, inside of a white sleeve box. Those materials are not around anymore. Had they been, I would be charging a bit more to make up what I paid for this originally, about a hundred dollars more. 

I will deal face to face, and will want to see a non-expired, valid Wisconsin drivers license. Recipient will be asked to sign the bill on sale as well. Please feel free to ask me any questions via email, or to set up an opportunity to see the gun. Thanks for looking!

postcontent: I am the original owner of this HK Mark 23. It has had only ~250 rounds of ammunition through it. The gun is in perfect condition without blemishes except for the normal wear mark that occurs on the top of the barrel as seen in the photos of the ejection port. The gun includes two 12 round magazines, two ten round magazines, the Mark 23 Picatinny Rail Adaptor ($129.95) for mounting a laser or tactical light such as the Surefire X400, and the GG&G Mark 23 Picatinny scope mount ($325) for mounting an Aimpoint, Holosight, or other sight of your choice, flash suppressor, original owners manual, warranty card, and HK fitted camo case. The HK Mark 23 Caliber .45 ACP pistol gives shooters match grade accuracy equal to that of the finest custom made handguns — yet exceeds the most stringent operational requirements ever demanded of a combat handgun. The Mark 23 provides match grade accuracy without the need for hand-fitted parts common in custom-built match pistols costing thousands of dollars more. One of the most thoroughly tested handguns in history, the MK23/Mark 23 project originated in 1991 when HK began development for the U.S. Special Operations Command, the organization that directs the activities of America's most elite military units, including the Navy SEALs and the Army Special Forces. On May 1, 1996, the first HK MK 23 pistols were delivered to the U.S. Special Operations Command for operational deployment, making the MK 23 the first caliber .45 ACP pistol to enter American military service since the venerable Government Model 1911A1. During testing, MK 23 pistols met the most stringent operational and accuracy requirements ever demanded of a combat handgun. Endurance testing demonstrated a service life of over 30,000 rounds of +P ammunition. To meet the reliability requirement, the pistol had to demonstrate a minimum of 2,000 mean rounds between stoppages (MRBS) with both M1911 ball and +P ammunition. All pistols exceeded the 2000 MRBS with an average of 6000 MRBS. In more than 450 accuracy test firings from a precision firing fixture at 25 meters, MK 23 pistols far exceeded the government requirement, averaging 1.44 inches, with 65 groups of less than one inch. There were four groups of .5 inches, with 5 rounds going through the same hole! The Mark 23 is available in .45 ACP Features: •	Threaded O-ring barrel with polygonal bore profile •	Match grade trigger •	One piece machined steel slide •	Frame mounted decocking lever and separate ambidextrous safety lever •	Can be carried “cocked and locked” in single action mode with the safety lever on •	Patented HK recoil reduction system •	Corrosion resistant blued finish •	Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame •	Oversized trigger guard for use with gloves •	Universal mounting grooves for installing accessories •	Ambidextrous magazine release lever •	Extended slide release •	Extractor doubles as a loaded chamber indicator •	Patented Lock-Out Safety device
